                  <h3>FAQ for Applicants</h3>

                  <p><strong>Do I have to answer all the questions to be considered?  Do I have to submit all the requested materials?</strong><br>
                  Questions marked with an asterisk (*) must be answered for consideration.  Other questions are meant to help program facilitators get a better picture of where you’re at in your development process.</p>
                  <p><strong>Do I have to be a Hawai’i resident entrepreneur to apply?</strong><br>
                  No, but keep in mind the Accelerator is targeting Hawai’i-based entrepreneurial teams/ Hawai’i owned transmedia companies & preference will be shown to candidates who demonstrate plans to produce products or to capture and retain the value of their IP in Hawai’i, or continue business activities in Hawai’i</p>
                  <p><strong>Can I apply if I’m not a US citizen?</strong><br>
                  Yes, but your startup company must be a US domiciled company.</p>
                  <p><strong>I am the only founder of my startup, can I still apply?</strong><br>
                  Yes, you may apply as a sole founder.  We do recommend, however, that you begin to look seriously for complementary team members to share the founding responsibilities and ownership with you.  Applicants will be considered, in part, based on the strength of the team.</p>
                  <p><strong>Can I apply if my idea is in its early stages of formation?</strong><br>
                  The GVS Transmedia Accelerator is geared towards transmedia companies who have already formed their story concept and have a script draft for their lead product.  For those who are in earlier stages of incubation and concept development, we recommend programs such as HIFF’s Creative Lab http://www.hiff.org/education/creative-lab</p>
                  <p><strong>Is my company already too developed to apply?</strong><br>
                  Probably not.  Any investment (time, finances, resources) you’ve already put into your startup will be maximized when supported, enhanced, and furthered by the acceleration process.  On the other hand, you may even discover some new strategies in connection with our Pipeline model and wish to make tweaks to your current plan.</p>
                  <p><strong>I’m submitting elements of my IP for review as a part of the application process and signed a waiver releasing GVS Transmedia Accelerator from liability.  Will my IP be protected?</strong><br>
                  Materials requested for review by the Accelerator Program will only be seen by those facilitating the Program and the selection process and for the express purpose of considering your application.</p>
